<headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 07 at 7:28PM MDT until July 07 at 8:15PM MDT by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 815 PM MDT
FOR NORTHWESTERN FERGUS AND EASTERN CHOUTEAU COUNTIES...
At 727 PM MDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from 17 miles northeast of Fort Benton to 11 miles east of
Geraldine, moving east at 35 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Hail damage to vehicles is expected. Expect wind damage to
roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations impacted include...
Geraldine, St. Pierre, Parker School, Square Butte, Judith Landing,
Iliad, Virgelle and Loma.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...1.00 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
